Rating: 3
I made this to use up some leftover creme fraiche and buttermilk I had in the fridge. I had no lemon juice, so I squeezed in half a grapefruit. I also followed a recent Cook's Illustrated tip and used a bit of corn syrup in place of some of the sugar. It came out great.

Rating: 2
I hate to be a naysayer here since everyone else loved this recipe, but I just didn't like the flavor. I have made Creme Fraiche ice cream before and admittedly, this recipe is way easier. But, on the down side, I thought it tasted like Buttermilk ice cream rather than the delicate Creme Fraiche.

